## Layout Consistency Rules

### Page Structure Requirements
All pages must follow a consistent layout structure to ensure uniform spacing and visual hierarchy across the entire application. Use the standard page pattern with proper content organization.

### Required Page Structure Pattern
Every page component should use this exact div structure:

```tsx
export default function YourPage() {
  return (
    <div className="space-y-6">
      {/* Header Section */}
      <div className="bg-white shadow rounded-lg p-6">
        <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Page Title</h1>
        <p className="text-gray-600">Page description</p>
      </div>

      {/* Additional content sections */}
      <div className="bg-white shadow rounded-lg p-6">
        {/* Content */}
      </div>
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Critical Layout Rules

1. **Root Container**: Always use `<div className="space-y-6">` as the root container for page content
2. **Content Cards**: Use `<div className="bg-white shadow rounded-lg p-6">` for content sections
3. **No Additional Containers**: Never add extra container divs, padding, or margins to pages
4. **Let MainLayout Handle Spacing**: The [MainLayout.tsx](mdc:server/app/components/MainLayout.tsx) component handles all page-level margins and padding

### Forbidden Practices

❌ **DO NOT** add these to any page:
- Extra container divs with padding/margins
- Custom margin or padding classes on the root page element
- Any layout-related styling that conflicts with MainLayout
- Page-specific spacing overrides

❌ **DO NOT** modify MainLayout margin values:
- The margin values in MainLayout.tsx have been carefully calibrated
- Never attempt to change `ml-72`, `ml-20`, `mr-2`, `mx-2`, or `pt-20` values
- These values ensure proper sidebar and navbar spacing

### Layout Consistency Benefits

✅ **Consistent Visual Hierarchy**: All pages have the same spacing and card structure
✅ **Responsive Design**: MainLayout handles all responsive behavior
✅ **Sidebar Integration**: Proper spacing for collapsed/expanded sidebar states
✅ **Navbar Integration**: Correct top padding for fixed navbar
✅ **Mobile Optimization**: Consistent mobile margins and spacing

